news.title: Gurugram: Builder submits bank guarantee, still no power supply in Ansal Esencia
news.para: Spread across 250 acres, the project was launched in 2011. Possession started in 2014 and there are currently around 2,000 families living there.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires Raj Kapoor's bungalow in Mumbai
news.para: In May 2019, Godrej Properties had acquired R.K. Studios from the Kapoor family, to develop a premium mixed-use project, Godrej RKS. The project is expected to be delivered in 2023.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels India asked to vacate unsafe Paradiso E, F towers
news.para: The District Town Planner (Enforcement) said in view of the dilapidated condition of these towers, if any untoward incident happens, the builder will be held responsible.

news.title: Noida authority seeks consent from 17 institutes for building audits
news.para: In November last year, the Authority Board had passed a structural audit policy for multi-storey buildings and made it compulsory for developers to submit a report after getting the highrises examined by an empanelled institute.

news.title: China Evergrande says directors fell 'below standards' in property unit probe
news.para: Evergrande said it was in talks with the unit to repay the funds involved. In July 2022, Evergrande revealed deposits of about 13.4 billion yuan ($1.96 billion) belonging to the property unit were used as collateral for pledge guarantees by the group.

news.title: China's new home prices rise in January 2023 for first time in a year
news.para: New home prices in January were up 0.1% month-on-month, versus a 0.2% slide in December, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data released on Thursday.

news.title: WeWork turns core profit in December 2022 for the first time since listing
news.para: Last month, WeWork said it planned to eliminate 300 roles across the countries. The New York-based company also announced its exit from 40 U.S. locations.

news.title: China: CIFI Group says has no debt payment problems, bonds jump
news.para: Shanghai-traded bonds issued by CIFI Group have been sharply down since late January, despite improved investor sentiment towards China's debt-crisis-battered property sector after authorities embarked on a slew of supportive measures.

news.title: Park Hotels plans to float Rs 1,500 crore-IPO in September 2023
news.para: The hotel chain had filed its draft red herring prospectus for a ₹1,000-crore IPO in January 2020 and received regulator's nod. However, the Covid-19 pandemic had postponed its IPO plans, first in March-April 2020 and again in April 2021.

news.title: Punjab to develop new urban estates in smaller towns
news.para: Arora also asked the officials to hold meetings with Resident Welfare Associations (RWAs) to conduct development works so that the residents don't face any hardship.

news.title: Co-working companies, tax experts ask government to simplify GST registration
news.para: Despite benefits and flexibility offered by the coworking operators, an evident roadblock was the denial of GST registration when the ‘principal place of business’ was applied for at such shared spaces.

news.title: Ambuja Cements declared as preferred bidder for Uskalvagu limestone block in Odisha
news.para: Uskalvagu limestone block is situated in Malkangiri district over an area of ~547 hectare with estimated limestone resource of ~141 million tonnes having average calcium oxide (CaO) content of 43.74 per cent.

news.title: Circle rate of land increased in Uttarakhand
news.para: While the circle rates are revised annually, the process was held for the past two years due to Covid-19. In 2023, the rates were revised for 57,000 areas across Uttarakhand. Across the total identified areas, the circle rate was increased by less than 50% in the majority of the areas.

news.title: Embassy REIT raises debt of Rs 1,000 crore from Bajaj Housing Finance
news.para: Embassy Office Parks REIT (Embassy REIT) will use the proceeds of this debt raise primarily to repay existing construction debt and for general corporate purposes.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA identifies 162 vacant plots, to sell them in phases
news.para: The urban development authority has so far conducted two rounds of auctions for a total 78 of these 162 vacant plots. The sale of 31 plots (out of the 78 that have been put to auction) fetched about Rs 35 crore to the VMRDA.
